<div id="ta186_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>In this test, students have to show that they can produce two different pieces of writing, a compulsory task and one of a choice.</p>
<p><b>What</b> <b>’</b> <b>s the test like?</b></p>
<p>The writing test consists of <b>2 parts</b> and the time allowed for both of them is <b>1 hour and 20 minutes</b>. The aim is to show that you can produce two different pieces of writing, such as letters, reports, reviews and short stories.</p>
<p><b>Advice for the Writing Paper:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Read carefully the instructions for the exam.</li>
<li>Use an appropriate style (formal/ informal) in a consistent way throughout the text.</li>
<li>Think first about the ideas you have to include, do not start writing straight away. Take a few minutes to write a few guidelines.</li>
<li>Write clearly.</li>
<li>Use a wide range of vocabulary.</li>
<li>Pay special attention to verb forms, prepositions, adverbs, etc.</li>
<li>Read your text at the end to find possible spelling mistakes.</li>
<li>Do not copy sentences from the input text.</li>
<li>Keep the number of words according to the exercise.</li>
<li>Don’t worry if you are used to American spelling, but keep it throughout the text. Do not mix American and British spelling.</li>
</ul>
